<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    How to force a zone update
From:       <a href="?a=95837786400020&r=1&w=2">dgis!generous () uunet ! uu ! net  (Curtis Generous)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198908">1989-08-11 11:41:56</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626982&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626982&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


Sometime back in April but not detected until recently, the serial number 
field of the SOA RR for my domain (daitc.mil) got messed up.  The result was 
that a serial number of 890000410 was propagated to the backup servers instead 
of 890410 (in case not obvious, the serial number is based on the date of the
update: 10-Apr-89).  No transfers have occurred since because of this problem.  

Is there a way of `forcing` an update or flushing out the bogus information 
without having to start using a new serial number scheme?
I have gone through all of the available docs but found no clues.

--curtis
-- 
